ON THIS EDITION OF BILL

00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:08.000
MOYERS "JOURNAL."

00:01:59.000 --> 00:02:01.000
FROM OUR STUDIOS IN NEW YORK,

00:02:01.000 --> 00:02:02.000
BILL

00:02:02.000 --> 00:02:03.000
Moyers: WELCOME TO THE

00:02:03.000 --> 00:02:04.000
"JOURNAL."

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:05.000
OUR SIX-YEAR-OLD GRANDSON IS A

00:02:05.000 --> 00:02:07.000
CELEBRATED ANT-CATCHER IN OUR

00:02:07.000 --> 00:02:08.000
HOUSEHOLD.

00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:09.000
HE GAVE ME THIS LATEST SPECIMEN

00:02:09.000 --> 00:02:10.000
FOR MY RECENT BIRTHDAY.

00:02:10.000 --> 00:02:11.000
I LOOK AT IT AND FIND MYSELF

00:02:11.000 --> 00:02:13.000
WONDERING THAT A CHILD'S

00:02:13.000 --> 00:02:14.000
CURIOSITY CAN LEAD TO A LIFETIME

00:02:14.000 --> 00:02:15.000
OF LEARNING, AND FINALLY TO AN

00:02:15.000 --> 00:02:16.000
ENCYCLOPEDIA OF ALL LIVING

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:18.000
THINGS.

00:02:18.000 --> 00:02:19.000
I'M NOT MAKING THAT UP.

00:02:19.000 --> 00:02:21.000
THAT'S EXACTLY WHAT HAPPENED TO

00:02:21.000 --> 00:02:23.000
E.O. WILSON.

00:02:23.000 --> 00:02:24.000
AS A BOY IN ALABAMA, HE

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:26.000
DISCOVERED THE FIRE ANT AND WENT

00:02:26.000 --> 00:02:28.000
ON TO BECOME ONE OF THE WORLD'S

00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:29.000
PREEMINENT SCIENTISTS, RENOWNED

00:02:29.000 --> 00:02:33.000
AS A BIOLOGIST, WITH 25 BOOKS TO

00:02:33.000 --> 00:02:34.000
HIS CREDIT, TWO PULITZER PRIZES

00:02:34.000 --> 00:02:37.000
AND HONORS GALORE.

00:02:37.000 --> 00:02:38.000
THE IVORY BILLED WOODPECKER

00:02:38.000 --> 00:02:42.000
COUNTS HIM A SOULMATE, AND

00:02:42.000 --> 00:02:43.000
THERE'S NOT AN ANTHILL IN THE

00:02:43.000 --> 00:02:44.000
WORLD THAT WOULDN'T RECOGNIZE

00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:45.000
HIM PEERING DOWN INTO IT.

00:02:45.000 --> 00:02:46.000
ALL THIS, A GREAT MARRIAGE, A

00:02:46.000 --> 00:02:48.000
FINE DAUGHTER, A FILM ON HIS

00:02:48.000 --> 00:02:49.000
LIFE IN THE MAKING.

00:02:49.000 --> 00:02:50.000
LAURELS TO REST ON FROM NOW TO

00:02:50.000 --> 00:02:51.000
KINGDOM COME, IF THERE IS ONE.

00:02:51.000 --> 00:02:52.000
NOW IN HIS EIGHTH DECADE, HE'S

00:02:52.000 --> 00:02:54.000
BEEN OFFERED ONE MORE WISH.

00:02:54.000 --> 00:02:55.000
YOU'RE ABOUT TO FIND OUT WHAT IT

00:02:55.000 --> 00:03:03.000
IS.

00:03:03.000 --> 00:03:04.000
THIS SHOULD BE A BIG SCIENCE

00:03:04.000 --> 00:03:08.000
PROJECT.

00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:08.000
Moyers: AT THE RECENT TED

00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:09.000
CONFERENCE-- AN ANNUAL GATHERING

00:03:09.000 --> 00:03:10.000
OF BIG THINKERS IN TECHNOLOGY,

00:03:10.000 --> 00:03:11.000
ENTERTAINMENT AND DESIGN-- E.O.

00:03:11.000 --> 00:03:11.000
WILSON WAS ASKED TO MAKE A WISH

00:03:11.000 --> 00:03:12.000
THAT COULD "CHANGE THE WORLD."

00:03:12.000 --> 00:03:14.000
THE SEARCH FOR LIFE TO

00:03:14.000 --> 00:03:15.000
UNDERSTAND IT AND FINALLY ABOVE

00:03:15.000 --> 00:03:17.000
ALL TO PRESERVE IT.

00:03:17.000 --> 00:03:19.000
THAT IS MY WISH AND LET US CALL

00:03:19.000 --> 00:03:23.000
IT THE ENCYCLOPEDIA OF LIFE.

00:03:23.000 --> 00:03:24.000
Moyers: HE SHOWED THEM A

00:03:24.000 --> 00:03:27.000
MOCK-UP OF WHAT HE HAS IN MIND;

00:03:27.000 --> 00:03:29.000
A DIGITAL ONLINE ENCYCLOPEDIA OF

00:03:29.000 --> 00:03:30.000
EVERY SINGLE LIVING SPECIES ON

00:03:30.000 --> 00:03:33.000
EARTH.

00:03:33.000 --> 00:03:34.000
SCIENTISTS AND LAYMEN EVERYWHERE

00:03:34.000 --> 00:03:36.000
COULD REFER TO IT AND WOULD BE

00:03:36.000 --> 00:03:39.000
ENCOURAGED TO CONTRIBUTE TO IT.

00:03:39.000 --> 00:03:41.000
IT WOULD START OUT AS A

00:03:41.000 --> 00:03:42.000
SCIENTIFIC COMPENDIUM OF

00:03:42.000 --> 00:03:44.000
EVERYTHING WE KNOW ABOUT A GIVEN

00:03:44.000 --> 00:03:46.000
SPECIES, AND BECOME A MAGNET FOR

00:03:46.000 --> 00:03:49.000
NEW INFORMATION, IMMEDIATELY

00:03:49.000 --> 00:03:51.000
TRANSLATED INTO MOST LANGUAGES,

00:03:51.000 --> 00:03:53.000
OPEN AND FREE TO EVERYONE FROM

00:03:53.000 --> 00:03:54.000
FIRST GRADERS TO BIOLOGISTS IN

00:03:54.000 --> 00:03:58.000
THE FIELD OR IN THE LABORATORY.

00:03:58.000 --> 00:03:59.000
IT'S ALWAYS BEEN A DREAM OF

00:03:59.000 --> 00:04:02.000
MINE, BILL, OF CLASSIFYING ALL

00:04:02.000 --> 00:04:04.000
THE SPECIES AND FINDING OUT WHAT

00:04:04.000 --> 00:04:06.000
MAKES UP THE BIOSPHERE.

00:04:06.000 --> 00:04:07.000
WE'RE MAYBE TODAY ABOUT ONE-

00:04:07.000 --> 00:04:10.000
TENTH THROUGH THE DISCOVERY OF

00:04:10.000 --> 00:04:11.000
SPECIES, MAYBE 90%--

00:04:11.000 --> 00:04:12.000
Moyers: THAT'S ALL WE KNOW

00:04:12.000 --> 00:04:13.000
TODAY?

00:04:13.000 --> 00:04:15.000
10% OF THE EXISTING SPECIES?

00:04:15.000 --> 00:04:15.000
YEAH.

00:04:15.000 --> 00:04:18.000
IT'S AMAZING, ISN'T IT?

00:04:18.000 --> 00:04:19.000
THAT WE DO NOT KNOW THE VAST

00:04:19.000 --> 00:04:22.000
MAJORITY OF KINDS OF ANIMALS

00:04:22.000 --> 00:04:23.000
MOSTLY AND MICROORGANISMS ON

00:04:23.000 --> 00:04:25.000
EARTH.

00:04:25.000 --> 00:04:27.000
WE LIVE IN AN UNEXPLORED PLANET.

00:04:27.000 --> 00:04:28.000
Moyers: WELL, THAT SHOWS HOW

00:04:28.000 --> 00:04:29.000
UNINFORMED I AM BECAUSE I

00:04:29.000 --> 00:04:30.000
FIGURED YOU ALL HAD PRETTY WELL

00:04:30.000 --> 00:04:32.000
MADE THE FINAL CENSUS OF

00:04:32.000 --> 00:04:33.000
EVERYTHING THAT'S ALIVE ON

00:04:33.000 --> 00:04:34.000
EARTH.

00:04:34.000 --> 00:04:37.000
WELL, YOU MAKE MY POINT.

00:04:37.000 --> 00:04:40.000
WE HAVE SCARCELY BEGUN.

00:04:40.000 --> 00:04:42.000
ONCE IT'S ONLINE, IT WILL ALLOW

00:04:42.000 --> 00:04:44.000
YOU TO GO TO YOUR COMPUTER

00:04:44.000 --> 00:04:47.000
ANYWHERE IN THE WORLD, SINGLE

00:04:47.000 --> 00:04:49.000
ACCESS ON COMMAND, PULL UP ANY

00:04:49.000 --> 00:04:52.000
SPECIES OUT OF THE TENS OF

00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:55.000
MILLIONS ON EARTH, PULL UP WAYS

00:04:55.000 --> 00:04:57.000
TO IDENTIFY SPECIES IF YOU HAVE

00:04:57.000 --> 00:05:02.000
A PLANT OR AN INSECT IN FRONT OF

00:05:02.000 --> 00:05:02.000
YOU NEED TO KNOW ABOUT, AND FIND

00:05:02.000 --> 00:05:04.000
OUT EVERYTHING THAT IS KNOWN

00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:06.000
ABOUT IT UP TO THAT TIME.

00:05:06.000 --> 00:05:07.000
Moyers: SORT OF A YOUTUBE OF

00:05:07.000 --> 00:05:09.000
BUGS, INSECTS, AND FUNGI, RIGHT?

00:05:09.000 --> 00:05:11.000
YES, AND EVERYTHING.

00:05:11.000 --> 00:05:11.000
Moyers: EVERYTHING.

00:05:11.000 --> 00:05:12.000
AND PEOPLE SAY THIS IS

00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:15.000
AMAZING, "THAT CAN'T BE DONE."

00:05:15.000 --> 00:05:16.000
I HAD RECENTLY--

00:05:16.000 --> 00:05:16.000
Moyers: YEAH, IT'S AMAZING,

00:05:16.000 --> 00:05:20.000
ED, IT CAN'T BE DONE.

00:05:20.000 --> 00:05:20.000
( LAUGHTER )

00:05:20.000 --> 00:05:21.000
WELL, A VERY DISTINGUISHED

00:05:21.000 --> 00:05:23.000
SCIENTIST WROTE ME RECENTLY WHEN

00:05:23.000 --> 00:05:25.000
I PUBLISHED AN ARTICLE ON THIS

00:05:25.000 --> 00:05:26.000
SEVERAL YEARS AGO, THAT THIS WAS

00:05:26.000 --> 00:05:28.000
WHAT WE MUST DO.

00:05:28.000 --> 00:05:30.000
AND HE SAYS LITERALLY "ED, WHAT

00:05:30.000 --> 00:05:33.000
HAVE YOU BEEN SMOKING?"

00:05:33.000 --> 00:05:34.000
( LAUGHTER )

00:05:34.000 --> 00:05:35.000
Moyers: SO I CAN SEE WHAT

00:05:35.000 --> 00:05:36.000
THIS WILL DO FOR THE PROTEGES OF

00:05:36.000 --> 00:05:37.000
ED WILSON.

00:05:37.000 --> 00:05:38.000
WHAT WILL IT DO FOR MY FIVE

00:05:38.000 --> 00:05:39.000
GRANDCHILDREN?

00:05:39.000 --> 00:05:41.000
A LOT.

00:05:41.000 --> 00:05:43.000
CONSIDER HOW IGNORANT WE ARE AND

00:05:43.000 --> 00:05:47.000
WHAT DIFFERENCE IT MAKES.

00:05:47.000 --> 00:05:50.000
WE DON'T KNOW THE GREAT MAJORITY

00:05:50.000 --> 00:05:52.000
OF THE KINDS OF CREATURES LIVING

00:05:52.000 --> 00:05:55.000
IN MOST PONDS OR PATCHES OF

00:05:55.000 --> 00:05:58.000
WOODS THAT YOU WOULD PICK EVEN

00:05:58.000 --> 00:06:01.000
AROUND HERE.

00:06:01.000 --> 00:06:01.000
THIS MEANS THAT WHEN WE'RE

00:06:01.000 --> 00:06:03.000
PLANNING THE ENVIRONMENT, WE'RE

00:06:03.000 --> 00:06:05.000
TRYING TO STABILIZE THE

00:06:05.000 --> 00:06:07.000
ENVIRONMENT, WE'RE TRYING TO GET

00:06:07.000 --> 00:06:08.000
SUSTAINABLE DEVELOPMENT, WE'RE

00:06:08.000 --> 00:06:09.000
TRYING TO STOP THE ECOSYSTEM

00:06:09.000 --> 00:06:10.000
FROM COLLAPSING IN THE FACE OF

00:06:10.000 --> 00:06:11.000
GLOBAL WARMING OR WHATEVER.

00:06:11.000 --> 00:06:13.000
WE REALLY NEED TO KNOW WHAT'S IN

00:06:13.000 --> 00:06:15.000
EACH ONE OF THOSE HABITATS.

00:06:15.000 --> 00:06:19.000
IT'S LIKE UNDERTAKING A MEDICAL

00:06:19.000 --> 00:06:22.000
EXAMINATION BY YOUR DOCTOR MAYBE

00:06:22.000 --> 00:06:23.000
NOT FEELING TOO WELL, YOU KNOW?

00:06:23.000 --> 00:06:25.000
SOMETHING'S HAPPENING, BUT YOUR

00:06:25.000 --> 00:06:26.000
DOCTOR EXAMINES YOU AND HE ONLY

00:06:26.000 --> 00:06:27.000
KNOWS 10% OF WHAT'S INSIDE YOU

00:06:27.000 --> 00:06:31.000
IN ALL OF THE ORGANS.

00:06:31.000 --> 00:06:33.000
WE NEED THEN TO MOVE ECOLOGY WAY

00:06:33.000 --> 00:06:34.000
AHEAD OF WHERE IT IS TODAY,

00:06:34.000 --> 00:06:37.000
REALLY CHANGE THINGS.

00:06:37.000 --> 00:06:38.000
Moyers: NO ONE IN OUR TIME

00:06:38.000 --> 00:06:40.000
HAS ADDED MORE TO OUR

00:06:40.000 --> 00:06:41.000
UNDERSTANDING OF EARTH'S ECOLOGY

00:06:41.000 --> 00:06:42.000
THAN ED WILSON.

00:06:42.000 --> 00:06:43.000
ONE OF THE WORLDS BEST KNOW

00:06:43.000 --> 00:06:45.000
SCIENTISTS, WILSON'S EXPLORATION

00:06:45.000 --> 00:06:46.000
OF NATURE STARTED IN MOBILE,

00:06:46.000 --> 00:06:48.000
ALABAMA.

00:06:48.000 --> 00:06:50.000
AS A 13-YEAR-OLD BOY, HE

00:06:50.000 --> 00:06:51.000
DISCOVERED THE VERY FIRST FIRE

00:06:51.000 --> 00:06:56.000
ANT COLONY IN THE UNITED STATES.

00:06:56.000 --> 00:06:57.000
WELL, I WAS AT THE PLACE

00:06:57.000 --> 00:06:57.000
WHERE THEY WERE FIRST

00:06:57.000 --> 00:06:58.000
INTRODUCED.

00:06:58.000 --> 00:06:59.000
I DISCOVERED THE FIRST COLONY OF

00:06:59.000 --> 00:07:01.000
FIRE ANTS IN THE LITTLE

00:07:01.000 --> 00:07:02.000
POPULATION WHEN IT WAS JUST

00:07:02.000 --> 00:07:02.000
BEGINNING TO SPREAD.

00:07:02.000 --> 00:07:03.000
Moyers: NEAR MOBILE?

00:07:03.000 --> 00:07:04.000
YEAH, IN MOBILE.

00:07:04.000 --> 00:07:06.000
WE LIVED FIVE BLOCKS FROM THE

00:07:06.000 --> 00:07:07.000
DOCK AREA.

00:07:07.000 --> 00:07:12.000
SO I CAUGHT ONE OF THE FIRST

00:07:12.000 --> 00:07:13.000
COLONIES WHEN IT WAS

00:07:13.000 --> 00:07:17.000
MULTIPLYING.

00:07:17.000 --> 00:07:18.000
IT BELONGS TO A GROUP OF SPECIES

00:07:18.000 --> 00:07:19.000
OF ANTS THAT ARE POTENTIALLY

00:07:19.000 --> 00:07:21.000
SERIOUS PESTS.

00:07:21.000 --> 00:07:22.000
Moyers: I THINK WE BOTH WOULD

00:07:22.000 --> 00:07:23.000
PROBABLY STILL BE LIVING IN THE

00:07:23.000 --> 00:07:24.000
SOUTH IF IT WEREN'T FOR THOSE

00:07:24.000 --> 00:07:24.000
INFERNAL FIRE ANTS, RIGHT?

00:07:24.000 --> 00:07:25.000
THAT'S RIGHT.

00:07:25.000 --> 00:07:26.000
THEY COME FROM URUGUAY, AND THEY

00:07:26.000 --> 00:07:27.000
JUST KEEP SPREADING.

00:07:27.000 --> 00:07:29.000
AND DOWN SOUTH, YOU KNOW, WE

00:07:29.000 --> 00:07:31.000
REFER TO THEM AS "FAR AIN'T,"

00:07:31.000 --> 00:07:33.000
AND THAT'S NOT DIALECT.

00:07:33.000 --> 00:07:34.000
IT MEANS THEY COME FROM FAR AWAY

00:07:34.000 --> 00:07:38.000
AND THEY AIN'T GOING HOME.

00:07:38.000 --> 00:07:39.000
( LAUGHTER )

00:07:39.000 --> 00:07:41.000
WELL, THERE ARE THOUSANDS AND

00:07:41.000 --> 00:07:42.000
THOUSANDS OF THESE SPECIES, AND

00:07:42.000 --> 00:07:43.000
SOME OF THEM REALLY AREN'T THAT

00:07:43.000 --> 00:07:45.000
FUNNY.

00:07:45.000 --> 00:07:46.000
Moyers: HE IS THE PREEMINENT

00:07:46.000 --> 00:07:48.000
EXPERT IN ANT BEHAVIOR AND

00:07:48.000 --> 00:07:49.000
COMMUNICATION.

00:07:49.000 --> 00:07:51.000
HIS RESEARCH ON THESE HIGHLY

00:07:51.000 --> 00:07:52.000
SOCIAL CREATURES HAS TAKEN HIM

00:07:52.000 --> 00:07:54.000
ACROSS THE GLOBE, FROM THE

00:07:54.000 --> 00:07:55.000
PACIFIC ISLANDS TO THE

00:07:55.000 --> 00:07:56.000
CARIBBEAN, AND HAS LEAD TO

00:07:56.000 --> 00:07:57.000
DISCOVERIES OF HUNDREDS OF NEW

00:07:57.000 --> 00:08:00.000
SPECIES.

00:08:00.000 --> 00:08:01.000
HIS CONTINUOUS WORK ON ANTS AND

00:08:01.000 --> 00:08:09.000
OTHER INSECTS HELPED FORM NEW

00:08:09.000 --> 00:08:09.000
SCIENTIFIC VIEWS ABOUT HOW

00:08:09.000 --> 00:08:10.000
ANIMALS AND HUMANS EVOLVE.

00:08:10.000 --> 00:08:11.000
NOT ALL ANT USE VIOLENCE TO

00:08:11.000 --> 00:08:12.000
DOMINATE THEIR WORLD.

00:08:12.000 --> 00:08:14.000
SOME USE MORE SUBTLE METHODS.

00:08:14.000 --> 00:08:16.000
Moyers: WHERE DID YOU GET

00:08:16.000 --> 00:08:17.000
THIS PASSION FOR ANTS?

00:08:17.000 --> 00:08:20.000
WHEN I WAS A KID.

00:08:20.000 --> 00:08:23.000
AS A LITTLE BOY THROUGH MY

00:08:23.000 --> 00:08:25.000
TEENAGE YEARS, I BECAME

00:08:25.000 --> 00:08:26.000
INCREASINGLY FASCINATED BY THE

00:08:26.000 --> 00:08:29.000
DIVERSITY OF LIFE.

00:08:29.000 --> 00:08:31.000
ONE DAY WHEN I WAS ONLY SEVEN

00:08:31.000 --> 00:08:34.000
YEARS AND FISHING, I PULLED A

00:08:34.000 --> 00:08:36.000
PIN FISH-- THEY'RE CALLED WITH

00:08:36.000 --> 00:08:39.000
SHARP DORSAL SPINES-- UP TOO

00:08:39.000 --> 00:08:40.000
HARD AND FAST AND I BLINDED

00:08:40.000 --> 00:08:43.000
MYSELF IN ONE EYE.

00:08:43.000 --> 00:08:44.000
I LATER DISCOVERED I WAS ALSO

00:08:44.000 --> 00:08:46.000
HARD OF HEARING, POSSIBLY

00:08:46.000 --> 00:08:47.000
CONGENITAL, IN THE UPPER

00:08:47.000 --> 00:08:49.000
REGISTER.

00:08:49.000 --> 00:08:51.000
SO WHEN PLANNING TO BE A

00:08:51.000 --> 00:08:53.000
PROFESSIONAL NATURALIST, I NEVER

00:08:53.000 --> 00:08:55.000
CONSIDERED ANYTHING ELSE IN MY

00:08:55.000 --> 00:08:57.000
ENTIRE LIFE.

00:08:57.000 --> 00:08:59.000
I FOUND I WAS LOUSY AT BIRD

00:08:59.000 --> 00:09:02.000
WATCHING AND COULDN'T TRACK FROG

00:09:02.000 --> 00:09:05.000
CALLS EITHER, SO I TURNED TO THE

00:09:05.000 --> 00:09:08.000
TEAMING SMALL CREATURES THAT CAN

00:09:08.000 --> 00:09:09.000
BE HELD BETWEEN THE THUMB AND

00:09:09.000 --> 00:09:13.000
FOREFINGER.

00:09:13.000 --> 00:09:15.000
THE LITTLE THINGS THAT COMPOSE

00:09:15.000 --> 00:09:17.000
THE FOUNDATION OF OUR

00:09:17.000 --> 00:09:19.000
ECOSYSTEMS.

00:09:19.000 --> 00:09:21.000
THE LITTLE THINGS THAT I LIKE TO

00:09:21.000 --> 00:09:24.000
SAY RUN THE WORLD.

00:09:24.000 --> 00:09:26.000
YOU KNOW, EVERY KID HAS A BUG

00:09:26.000 --> 00:09:27.000
PERIOD AND I NEVER GREW OUT OF

00:09:27.000 --> 00:09:29.000
MINE.

00:09:29.000 --> 00:09:31.000
I JUST STARTED, AS MOST KIDS DO,

00:09:31.000 --> 00:09:33.000
YOU KNOW, CATCHING BUGS AND

00:09:33.000 --> 00:09:36.000
FROGS IN BOTTLES AND SO ON.

00:09:36.000 --> 00:09:37.000
Moyers: WHEN THE WILSON

00:09:37.000 --> 00:09:38.000
FAMILY MOVED NORTH, HE CARRIED

00:09:38.000 --> 00:09:39.000
HIS CURIOSITY ABOUT NATURE WITH

00:09:39.000 --> 00:09:40.000
HIM.

00:09:40.000 --> 00:09:42.000
HIS FAMILY SETTLED IN A PLACE

00:09:42.000 --> 00:09:43.000
PERFECT FOR A BUDDING

00:09:43.000 --> 00:09:45.000
NATURALIST.

00:09:45.000 --> 00:09:48.000
I WAS IN WASHINGTON, D.C. AND

00:09:48.000 --> 00:09:50.000
PROVIDENTIALLY WE LIVED WITHIN

00:09:50.000 --> 00:09:52.000
WALKING DISTANCE OF ROCK CREEK

00:09:52.000 --> 00:09:56.000
PARK AND THE WASHINGTON ZOO.

00:09:56.000 --> 00:09:58.000
SO A CHILD INTERESTED IN INSECTS

