EVOLUTION ALWAYS PROVIDED NEW

00:19:02.000 --> 00:19:05.000
SPECIES."

00:19:05.000 --> 00:19:06.000
WELL, THE PROBLEM WITH THAT IS

00:19:06.000 --> 00:19:07.000
THE BIRTH RATE OF SPECIES IS

00:19:07.000 --> 00:19:08.000
GOING DOWN.

00:19:08.000 --> 00:19:09.000
WHY IS IT GOING DOWN?

00:19:09.000 --> 00:19:11.000
BECAUSE WE'RE DESTROYING THE

00:19:11.000 --> 00:19:12.000
CRADLES IN WHICH NEW SPECIES ARE

00:19:12.000 --> 00:19:16.000
BORN, THE NATURAL ENVIRONMENT.

00:19:16.000 --> 00:19:19.000
SO WHAT DIFFERENCE DOES IT MAKE?

00:19:19.000 --> 00:19:21.000
WELL, IF HUMANITY AS A WHOLE

00:19:21.000 --> 00:19:22.000
DECIDED THAT IT WANTS TO LIVE IN

00:19:22.000 --> 00:19:27.000
A WORLD WHERE EVERYTHING IS

00:19:27.000 --> 00:19:30.000
ARTIFACTUAL AND THE PRODUCT OF

00:19:30.000 --> 00:19:31.000
OUR BRAINS WE GIVE AWAY THIS

00:19:31.000 --> 00:19:33.000
GREAT HERITAGE AND ALL OF THIS

00:19:33.000 --> 00:19:34.000
MYSTERY AND BEAUTY AND

00:19:34.000 --> 00:19:37.000
COMPLEXITY THAT WE HAVEN'T EVEN

00:19:37.000 --> 00:19:38.000
BEGUN TO EXPLORE, WELL, I GUESS

00:19:38.000 --> 00:19:39.000
IF THAT'S WHAT PEOPLE WANT,

00:19:39.000 --> 00:19:40.000
THAT'S WHAT THEY'RE GOING TO

00:19:40.000 --> 00:19:42.000
GET.

