Moyers: LISTENING TO E.O.

00:36:57.000 --> 00:36:58.000
WILSON, MY COLLEAGUES AND I

00:36:58.000 --> 00:36:59.000
FOUND OURSELVES TALKING ABOUT

00:36:59.000 --> 00:37:01.000
DIAMOND TEAGUE.

00:37:01.000 --> 00:37:02.000
DIAMOND TEAGUE CAME INTO OUR

00:37:02.000 --> 00:37:03.000
LIVES THREE AND A HALF YEARS AGO

00:37:03.000 --> 00:37:05.000
IN A REPORT ABOUT SOME KIDS WHO

00:37:05.000 --> 00:37:06.000
LIVE IN THE SHADOW OF THE U.S.

00:37:06.000 --> 00:37:08.000
CAPITOL, BUT MIGHT AS WELL BE ON

00:37:08.000 --> 00:37:09.000
THE FAR SIDE OF THE MOON FOR ALL

00:37:09.000 --> 00:37:12.000
OFFICIAL WASHINGTON CARES.

00:37:12.000 --> 00:37:13.000
THEY LIVE IN AN IMPOVERISHED

00:37:13.000 --> 00:37:15.000
NEIGHBORHOOD, RIDDLED WITH

00:37:15.000 --> 00:37:17.000
VIOLENCE AND TOXIC WASTE.

00:37:17.000 --> 00:37:18.000
A RIVER FLOWS THROUGH IT, DIRTY

00:37:18.000 --> 00:37:20.000
AND DANGEROUS FROM POLLUTION.

00:37:20.000 --> 00:37:22.000
DIAMOND TEAGUE AND HIS PALS

00:37:22.000 --> 00:37:23.000
FOUND MEANING IN THEIR LIVES AS

00:37:23.000 --> 00:37:25.000
THEY SET OUT TO CLEAN UP THE

00:37:25.000 --> 00:37:26.000
RIVER AND REDEEM THEIR

00:37:26.000 --> 00:37:27.000
COMMUNITY.

00:37:27.000 --> 00:37:28.000
THIS REPORT ON THE EARTH

00:37:28.000 --> 00:37:29.000
CONSERVATION CORPS WAS PRODUCED

00:37:29.000 --> 00:37:31.000
BY WILLIAM BRANGHAM AND REPORTED

00:37:31.000 --> 00:37:34.000
BY NPR's DANIEL ZWERDLING.

00:37:34.000 --> 00:37:35.000
Reporter: DARIUS PHILLIPS

00:37:35.000 --> 00:37:37.000
WOULD BE THE FIRST TO TELL YOU

00:37:37.000 --> 00:37:38.000
THAT HE WAS THE KIND OF MAN YOU

00:37:38.000 --> 00:37:40.000
SHOULD BE AFRAID OF.

00:37:40.000 --> 00:37:41.000
PEOPLE ON THE STREETS HERE IN

00:37:41.000 --> 00:37:43.000
WASHINGTON, D.C. USED TO CALL

00:37:43.000 --> 00:37:45.000
HIM "THE BIG HURT."

00:37:45.000 --> 00:37:46.000
AND YOU COULD SAY SOMETHING

00:37:46.000 --> 00:37:47.000
ABOUT, SAY SOMETHING TO ME, YOU

00:37:47.000 --> 00:37:48.000
DIDN'T EVEN HAVE TO SAY

00:37:48.000 --> 00:37:49.000
ANYTHING, YOU COULD LOOK AT ME A

00:37:49.000 --> 00:37:51.000
DIFFERENT WAY, AND I'M DOWN YOUR

00:37:51.000 --> 00:37:53.000
NECK, JUST LIKE THAT.

00:37:53.000 --> 00:37:54.000
Reporter: PHILLIPS SOLD

00:37:54.000 --> 00:37:55.000
CRACK, HE STOLE CARS, HE ROBBED

00:37:55.000 --> 00:37:58.000
TAXI DRIVERS.

00:37:58.000 --> 00:38:00.000
HE'S 22 YEARS OLD.

00:38:00.000 --> 00:38:01.000
MY WHOLE PHILOSOPHY AT THAT

00:38:01.000 --> 00:38:03.000
PARTICULAR TIME WAS NEVER LEAVE

00:38:03.000 --> 00:38:04.000
THE HOUSE WITH LESS THAN $5,000

00:38:04.000 --> 00:38:06.000
ON YOU.

00:38:06.000 --> 00:38:07.000
YOU KNOW, THAT'S LIKE, THAT WAS

00:38:07.000 --> 00:38:09.000
MY QUOTA FOR THE DAY.

00:38:09.000 --> 00:38:10.000
I GOT TO PUT TEN IN THE BANK

00:38:10.000 --> 00:38:11.000
EVERY DAY, AND I ALWAYS GOT TO

00:38:11.000 --> 00:38:12.000
WALK AROUND WITH FIVE IN MY

00:38:12.000 --> 00:38:15.000
POCKET, EVERY DAY.

00:38:15.000 --> 00:38:16.000
Reporter: LASHAUNTYA MOORE IS

00:38:16.000 --> 00:38:17.000
A 24-YEAR-OLD WELFARE MOTHER.

00:38:17.000 --> 00:38:19.000
HER BROTHER'S IN PRISON FOR

00:38:19.000 --> 00:38:21.000
DOUBLE HOMICIDE.

00:38:21.000 --> 00:38:22.000
SHE STARTED HAVING BABIES WHEN

00:38:22.000 --> 00:38:25.000
SHE WAS IN HIGH SCHOOL.

00:38:25.000 --> 00:38:26.000
I HAD THAT FANTASY THAT THE

00:38:26.000 --> 00:38:27.000
GUY, HE LOVED ME AND WE WERE

00:38:27.000 --> 00:38:29.000
GOING TO GET MARRIED AND WE WERE

00:38:29.000 --> 00:38:31.000
GOING TO HAVE A BIG HOUSE AND

00:38:31.000 --> 00:38:32.000
TAKE CARE OF OUR BABY.

00:38:32.000 --> 00:38:33.000
WE WERE GOING TO HAVE A GOOD

00:38:33.000 --> 00:38:34.000
LIFE AND WE WERE GOING TO BE

00:38:34.000 --> 00:38:36.000
HAPPY.

00:38:36.000 --> 00:38:37.000
SO, THAT WAS MY PLAN.

00:38:37.000 --> 00:38:39.000
AND I TOLD THAT TO MY FATHER.

00:38:39.000 --> 00:38:40.000
AND HE WAS LIKE, "YOU'RE LIVING

00:38:40.000 --> 00:38:42.000
IN A DREAM WORLD."

00:38:42.000 --> 00:38:43.000
Reporter: THERE'S NOT MUCH

00:38:43.000 --> 00:38:44.000
REASON TO EXPECT THAT THESE

00:38:44.000 --> 00:38:46.000
YOUNG PEOPLE WOULD EVER MAKE IT

00:38:46.000 --> 00:38:48.000
OUT OF THIS WORLD.

00:38:48.000 --> 00:38:49.000
BUT NOW THEY'RE TRYING TO

00:38:49.000 --> 00:38:51.000
TRANSFORM THEIR LIVES AND

00:38:51.000 --> 00:38:53.000
THEY'RE DOING IT PARTLY BY

00:38:53.000 --> 00:38:54.000
TRANSFORMING THE AREA WHERE THEY

00:38:54.000 --> 00:38:56.000
LIVE.

00:38:56.000 --> 00:38:58.000
WE'RE GOING TO FOCUS ON THIS

00:38:58.000 --> 00:38:59.000
AREA, CLEANUP ON THE EXTERIOR OF

00:38:59.000 --> 00:39:00.000
THE GATE.

00:39:00.000 --> 00:39:01.000
Reporter: A FEW MONTHS AGO,

00:39:01.000 --> 00:39:03.000
THEY JOINED A NON-PROFIT PROGRAM

00:39:03.000 --> 00:39:04.000
CALLED THE EARTH CONSERVATION

00:39:04.000 --> 00:39:06.000
CORPS.

00:39:06.000 --> 00:39:08.000
THE BASIC IDEA SOUNDS SIMPLE:

00:39:08.000 --> 00:39:09.000
YOU RECRUIT A FEW DOZEN YOUNG

00:39:09.000 --> 00:39:11.000
MEN AND WOMEN FROM THE

00:39:11.000 --> 00:39:12.000
COMMUNITY-- EVEN IF THEY HAVE

00:39:12.000 --> 00:39:13.000
CRIMINAL RECORDS OR IF THEY'RE

00:39:13.000 --> 00:39:15.000
DROP-OUTS-- AND YOU HIRE THEM TO

00:39:15.000 --> 00:39:16.000
CLEAN UP AND RESTORE THEIR

00:39:16.000 --> 00:39:18.000
NEIGHBORHOOD.

00:39:18.000 --> 00:39:20.000
BUT NOTHING IS SIMPLE IN THIS

00:39:20.000 --> 00:39:24.000
PART OF THE NATION'S CAPITAL.

00:39:24.000 --> 00:39:25.000
BECAUSE WE'RE NOT TALKING ABOUT

00:39:25.000 --> 00:39:27.000
THIS WASHINGTON ON THE BANKS OF

00:39:27.000 --> 00:39:29.000
THE SHINING POTOMAC RIVER; WE'RE

00:39:29.000 --> 00:39:30.000
TALKING ABOUT THIS WASHINGTON ON

00:39:30.000 --> 00:39:33.000
THE BANKS OF THE OTHER RIVER.

00:39:33.000 --> 00:39:35.000
THEY CALL THE RIVER AND THE

00:39:35.000 --> 00:39:37.000
NEIGHBORHOOD ANACOSTIA.

00:39:37.000 --> 00:39:38.000
MOST CALL THIS WHOLE AREA

00:39:38.000 --> 00:39:40.000
"SOUTHEAST."

00:39:40.000 --> 00:39:42.000
IT'S ONLY A FEW BLOCKS FROM THE

00:39:42.000 --> 00:39:43.000
U.S. CAPITOL, BUT IT'S ONE OF

00:39:43.000 --> 00:39:45.000
THE WORST NEIGHBORHOODS IN

00:39:45.000 --> 00:39:47.000
AMERICA.

00:39:47.000 --> 00:39:49.000
WHEN WE CAME HERE, YOU

00:39:49.000 --> 00:39:50.000
COULDN'T SEE THE RIVER STANDING

00:39:50.000 --> 00:39:52.000
HERE.

00:39:52.000 --> 00:39:53.000
THERE WERE TRASH HEAPS 100 FEET

00:39:53.000 --> 00:39:55.000
HIGH.

00:39:55.000 --> 00:39:56.000
Reporter: BOB NIXON USED TO

00:39:56.000 --> 00:39:58.000
BE A HOLLYWOOD PRODUCER.

00:39:58.000 --> 00:40:00.000
HE CAME TO WASHINGTON IN THE

00:40:00.000 --> 00:40:02.000
EARLY 1990s, TO SHOOT A FILM

00:40:02.000 --> 00:40:03.000
ABOUT THE ENVIRONMENT.

00:40:03.000 --> 00:40:04.000
NIXON STAYED AND HE SET UP THE

00:40:04.000 --> 00:40:06.000
EARTH CONSERVATION CORPS,

00:40:06.000 --> 00:40:07.000
BECAUSE HE FELT HE HAD TO DO

00:40:07.000 --> 00:40:08.000
SOMETHING ABOUT THIS

00:40:08.000 --> 00:40:09.000
ENVIRONMENT.

00:40:09.000 --> 00:40:11.000
THEY DIDN'T JUST DUMP TRASH

00:40:11.000 --> 00:40:13.000
HERE, THEY DUMPED PEOPLE HERE.

00:40:13.000 --> 00:40:15.000
THERE ARE, YOU KNOW, 90% OF THE

00:40:15.000 --> 00:40:16.000
PUBLIC HOUSING COMMUNITIES IN

00:40:16.000 --> 00:40:17.000
WASHINGTON ARE, YOU KNOW, WITHIN

00:40:17.000 --> 00:40:19.000
A MILE AND A HALF OF THIS DUMP

00:40:19.000 --> 00:40:21.000
RIGHT HERE.

00:40:21.000 --> 00:40:22.000
Reporter: EVERY CITY HAS A

00:40:22.000 --> 00:40:24.000
PLACE LIKE SOUTHEAST.

00:40:24.000 --> 00:40:26.000
THIS IS WHERE THEY PUT THE

00:40:26.000 --> 00:40:27.000
PROJECTS, THIS IS WHERE THEY PUT

00:40:27.000 --> 00:40:29.000
THE FACTORIES AND THE FREEWAYS.

00:40:29.000 --> 00:40:30.000
THIS IS WHERE EVERYBODY PUTS

00:40:30.000 --> 00:40:33.000
THEIR POLLUTION.

00:40:33.000 --> 00:40:34.000
BUT THE KILLINGS ALONG THESE

00:40:34.000 --> 00:40:36.000
STREETS GIVE WASHINGTON ITS

00:40:36.000 --> 00:40:38.000
HORRENDOUS DISTINCTION: IT HAS

00:40:38.000 --> 00:40:39.000
THE HIGHEST MURDER RATE OF ANY

00:40:39.000 --> 00:40:43.000
MAJOR CITY IN THE COUNTRY.

00:40:43.000 --> 00:40:45.000
EVERY DAY, EVERY DAY, YOU

00:40:45.000 --> 00:40:46.000
KNOW, "SUCH AND SUCH DIED."

00:40:46.000 --> 00:40:48.000
YOU KNOW, "SUCH AND SUCH DIED."

00:40:48.000 --> 00:40:49.000
TWO FRIENDS OF MINE WERE

00:40:49.000 --> 00:40:50.000
KILLED.

00:40:50.000 --> 00:40:51.000
AND MY UNCLE WAS SHOT UP AT THE

00:40:51.000 --> 00:40:54.000
SAME TIME.

00:40:54.000 --> 00:40:55.000
HE WAS SHOT IN THE STOMACH WITH

00:40:55.000 --> 00:40:57.000
AN A.K.

00:40:57.000 --> 00:40:58.000
MY SENIOR YEAR OF HIGH SCHOOL

00:40:58.000 --> 00:41:00.000
I HAD TO GO TO 11 FUNERALS.

00:41:00.000 --> 00:41:03.000
MY SENIOR YEAR OF HIGH SCHOOL.

00:41:03.000 --> 00:41:05.000
Reporter: THESE YOUNG PEOPLE

00:41:05.000 --> 00:41:06.000
SAY WHEN THEY FIRST HEARD ABOUT

00:41:06.000 --> 00:41:07.000
THE EARTH CONSERVATION CORPS,

00:41:07.000 --> 00:41:08.000
THE LAST THING THE CARED ABOUT

00:41:08.000 --> 00:41:12.000
WAS CLEANING UP THE ENVIRONMENT.

00:41:12.000 --> 00:41:13.000
THEY WERE LOOKING FOR A WAY TO

00:41:13.000 --> 00:41:14.000
SURVIVE.

00:41:14.000 --> 00:41:16.000
THE CORPS PAYS ROUGHLY MINIMUM

00:41:16.000 --> 00:41:18.000
WAGE, PLUS THEY GET HEALTH

00:41:18.000 --> 00:41:20.000
INSURANCE AND A $5,000

00:41:20.000 --> 00:41:21.000
SCHOLARSHIP IF THEY GO BACK TO

00:41:21.000 --> 00:41:23.000
SCHOOL.

00:41:23.000 --> 00:41:24.000
BUT SOMETHING CLICKS WHEN THEY

00:41:24.000 --> 00:41:27.000
GET OUT ON THE ANACOSTIA.

00:41:27.000 --> 00:41:29.000
THEY GO ABOUT A MILE UPSTREAM,

00:41:29.000 --> 00:41:30.000
AND THEY SEE THEIR COMMUNITY IN

00:41:30.000 --> 00:41:33.000
A NEW WAY.

00:41:33.000 --> 00:41:34.000
BASICALLY LIKE FIVE, TEN

00:41:34.000 --> 00:41:36.000
MINUTES AWAY, I LIVE FROM HERE.

00:41:36.000 --> 00:41:38.000
AND THIS IS... THIS IS NOT ALL I

00:41:38.000 --> 00:41:39.000
KNOW, BUT THIS IS WHERE, THIS ISçó

00:41:39.000 --> 00:41:39.000
A PART OF ME.

00:41:39.000 --> 00:41:42.000
THIS IS MY HERITAGE.

00:41:42.000 --> 00:41:44.000
AND TO BE A PART OF SOMETHING SO

00:41:44.000 --> 00:41:45.000
BEAUTIFUL, IT'S OVERWHELMING

00:41:45.000 --> 00:41:47.000
WHEN YOU LOOK AT IT AROUND HERE,

00:41:47.000 --> 00:41:48.000
AND YOU CAN SAY THAT I'M A PART

00:41:48.000 --> 00:41:50.000
OF SOMETHING SO BEAUTIFUL.

00:41:50.000 --> 00:41:51.000
Reporter: PHILLIPS AND THE

00:41:51.000 --> 00:41:53.000
OTHER CORPS MEMBERS TAKE VIDEOS

00:41:53.000 --> 00:41:54.000
WHEREVER THEY GO SO THEY CAN

00:41:54.000 --> 00:41:55.000
DOCUMENT THEIR HERITAGE AND SHOW

00:41:55.000 --> 00:41:57.000
HOW THEY'RE TRYING TO SAVE IT.

00:41:57.000 --> 00:41:59.000
I'M AT THE MOUTH OF BEAVER

00:41:59.000 --> 00:42:01.000
DAM RIGHT NOW, READY TO TAKE

00:42:01.000 --> 00:42:02.000
THREE MORE WATER SAMPLES.

00:42:02.000 --> 00:42:04.000
Reporter: THE PROBLEM IS,

00:42:04.000 --> 00:42:06.000
THIS RIVER HAS BECOME ONE OF

00:42:06.000 --> 00:42:08.000
MOST POLLUTED IN AMERICA.

00:42:08.000 --> 00:42:09.000
YOU CAN'T TELL BY LOOKING AT IT,

00:42:09.000 --> 00:42:10.000
BUT HEALTH OFFICIALS ESTIMATE

00:42:10.000 --> 00:42:12.000
THAT MORE THAN A BILLION GALLONS

00:42:12.000 --> 00:42:13.000
OF RAW SEWAGE END UP IN THE

00:42:13.000 --> 00:42:16.000
ANACOSTIA, EVERY YEAR.

00:42:16.000 --> 00:42:17.000
TODAY, THE CORPS IS GOING OUT ON

00:42:17.000 --> 00:42:20.000
ONE OF ITS REGULAR PATROLS.

00:42:20.000 --> 00:42:22.000
THEY'VE HEARD THAT RAW SEWAGE

00:42:22.000 --> 00:42:23.000
MIGHT BE POURING INTO A

00:42:23.000 --> 00:42:24.000
TRIBUTARY ILLEGALLY, AND THEY'RE

00:42:24.000 --> 00:42:27.000
INVESTIGATING.

00:42:27.000 --> 00:42:28.000
WHEN THEY FIND SUSPECT DUMPING,

00:42:28.000 --> 00:42:30.000
THEY REPORT IT.

00:42:30.000 --> 00:42:31.000
MY NAME IS JEROME GLOVER OF

00:42:31.000 --> 00:42:34.000
THE EARTH CONSERVATION CORPS.

00:42:34.000 --> 00:42:35.000
THIS IS THE FIRST DAY OF OUR

00:42:35.000 --> 00:42:38.000
TESTING OF THE WATER QUALITY.

00:42:38.000 --> 00:42:40.000
WHAT DO YOU THINK THIS IS?

00:42:40.000 --> 00:42:42.000
I HAVE NO IDEA WHAT IT IS.

00:42:42.000 --> 00:42:43.000
IT HASN'T RAINED IN LIKE, FOUR

00:42:43.000 --> 00:42:47.000
OR FIVE DAYS.

00:42:47.000 --> 00:42:51.000
IN 24 HOURS, WE'LL KNOW.

00:42:51.000 --> 00:42:53.000
Reporter: AND THE NEXT

00:42:53.000 --> 00:42:54.000
MORNING, THE RESULTS CONFIRM

00:42:54.000 --> 00:42:56.000
WHAT THEY SUSPECTED.

00:42:56.000 --> 00:42:57.000
THESE BIG GLOPS RIGHT HERE,

00:42:57.000 --> 00:43:00.000
IT SHOWS THAT THE ANACOSTIA IS

00:43:00.000 --> 00:43:01.000
CONTAMINATED WITH FECAL

00:43:01.000 --> 00:43:02.000
COLIFORMS.

00:43:02.000 --> 00:43:02.000
Reporter: FECAL WHAT?

00:43:02.000 --> 00:43:04.000
COLIFORM.

00:43:04.000 --> 00:43:05.000
IT'S... IT'S LIKE HUMAN CRAP,

00:43:05.000 --> 00:43:08.000
FOR REAL.

00:43:08.000 --> 00:43:09.000
SO, YEAH, AND THERE IT IS RIGHT

00:43:09.000 --> 00:43:12.000
THERE.

00:43:12.000 --> 00:43:13.000
Reporter: BOB NIXON SAYS

00:43:13.000 --> 00:43:14.000
THESE CORPS MEMBERS ARE DOING

00:43:14.000 --> 00:43:16.000
SOME OF THE WORK THEIR

00:43:16.000 --> 00:43:17.000
GOVERNMENT SHOULD BE DOING.

00:43:17.000 --> 00:43:19.000
THIS IS, IN A LOT OF SENSE,

00:43:19.000 --> 00:43:21.000
GROUND ZERO FOR A LOT OF ISSUES

00:43:21.000 --> 00:43:22.000
THAT ARE FACING OUR WHOLE

00:43:22.000 --> 00:43:23.000
COUNTRY.

00:43:23.000 --> 00:43:25.000
THEY'RE FIGHTING

00:43:25.000 --> 00:43:26.000
ENVIRONMENTAL... PEOPLE CALL IT

00:43:26.000 --> 00:43:27.000
"ENVIRONMENTAL JUSTICE," I THINK

00:43:27.000 --> 00:43:29.000
IT'S "ENVIRONMENTAL INJUSTICE."

00:43:29.000 --> 00:43:31.000
ALL SORTS OF SORT OF INJUSTICES

00:43:31.000 --> 00:43:33.000
PILED ONE ON TOP OF THE OTHER

00:43:33.000 --> 00:43:36.000
THAT THEY'RE TRYING TO UNTANGLE.

00:43:36.000 --> 00:43:37.000
Reporter: WHEN YOU TALK TO

00:43:37.000 --> 00:43:38.000
CORPS MEMBERS, THEY ALL GIVE

00:43:38.000 --> 00:43:39.000
DIFFERENT REASONS WHY THEY'RE

00:43:39.000 --> 00:43:41.000
CAUGHT UP IN THIS WORK.

00:43:41.000 --> 00:43:42.000
I LOVE THE RESEARCH, BECAUSE

00:43:42.000 --> 00:43:43.000
IT'S FUN.

00:43:43.000 --> 00:43:45.000
IT'S LIKE BEING A DETECTIVE.

00:43:45.000 --> 00:43:46.000
YOU GET TO FIND OUT WHO'S

00:43:46.000 --> 00:43:48.000
ACTUALLY DOING WHAT, AND WE CAN

00:43:48.000 --> 00:43:49.000
WRITE LETTERS AND GET THINGS TO

00:43:49.000 --> 00:43:51.000
HAPPEN.

00:43:51.000 --> 00:43:52.000
Reporter: ANOTHER CORPS

00:43:52.000 --> 00:43:53.000
MEMBER, JEROME SCOTT, SAYS HE

00:43:53.000 --> 00:43:55.000
WANTS TO PROTECT WILDLIFE ALONG

00:43:55.000 --> 00:43:56.000
THIS RIVER.

00:43:56.000 --> 00:43:58.000
I WANT TO BE A ZOOLOGIST, A

00:43:58.000 --> 00:43:59.000
MARINE BIOLOGIST, ANYTHING THAT

00:43:59.000 --> 00:44:01.000
HAS TO DO WITH ANIMALS.

00:44:01.000 --> 00:44:03.000
I LOVE IT.

00:44:03.000 --> 00:44:04.000
Reporter: ACTUALLY, HE'S

00:44:04.000 --> 00:44:05.000
ALREADY TEACHING A BIT OF

00:44:05.000 --> 00:44:07.000
SCIENCE.

00:44:07.000 --> 00:44:08.000
JUST ABOUT EVERY MORNING,

00:44:08.000 --> 00:44:10.000
MEMBERS OF THE EARTH

00:44:10.000 --> 00:44:11.000
CONSERVATION CORPS AND ANOTHER

00:44:11.000 --> 00:44:12.000
NONPROFIT GROUP TAKE STUDENTS

00:44:12.000 --> 00:44:13.000
FROM LOCAL SCHOOLS OUT ON THE

00:44:13.000 --> 00:44:15.000
RIVER.

00:44:15.000 --> 00:44:16.000
THEY'RE TEACHING THE NEXT

00:44:16.000 --> 00:44:17.000
GENERATION ABOUT THE

00:44:17.000 --> 00:44:18.000
ENVIRONMENT.

00:44:18.000 --> 00:44:20.000
DAVID SMITH HELPS RUN THE CORPS.

00:44:20.000 --> 00:44:21.000
HE'S PICKED JEROME SCOTT TO BE

00:44:21.000 --> 00:44:23.000
ONE OF THE GUIDES.

00:44:23.000 --> 00:44:25.000
